#: ../../B/Bzzzt-Wrong.rst:5
msgid "Bzzzt! Wrong."
msgstr "Bzzzt! Wrong."

#: ../../B/Bzzzt-Wrong.rst:7
msgid "/bzt rong/, excl\\."
msgstr "/bzt rong/, 感嘆詞"

#: ../../B/Bzzzt-Wrong.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common; Usenet/Internet; punctuation varies] From a Robin Williams routine "
"in the movie *Dead Poets Society* spoofing radio or TV quiz programs, such "
"as *Truth or Consequences*\\, where an incorrect answer earns one a blast "
"from the buzzer and condolences from the interlocutor. A way of expressing "
"mock-rude disagreement, usually immediately following an included quote from"
" another poster. The less abbreviated \"\\*Bzzzzt\\*, wrong, but thank you "
"for playing\" is also common; capitalization and emphasis of the buzzer "
"sound varies."
msgstr ""
"[一般的。Usenet/Internet。句読点は様々]映画\\ *Dead Poets Society*\\ におけるRobin "
"Williamsの一場面に由来する。これは\\ *Truth or Consequences*\\ "
"のようなラジオやテレビのクイズ番組をもじったもので、不正解には司会者からブザーの一吹きとお悔やみが贈られる。冗談めかして無礼に異議を唱える言い方で、たいてい他の投稿者からの引用の直後に置かれる。あまり略さない「\\*Bzzzzt\\*,"
" wrong, but thank you for "
"playing(ブー、不正解、でも参加ありがとう)」も一般的である。ブザー音の大文字化と強調は様々である。"
